>Fast, being good for running messages, escaping danger, hunting, and that often neglected aspect that makes the difference between life and death: RECON
>Ambush predator instincts allow you and her to coordinate attacks and catch prey
>Light enough to easily carry if she ever gets hurt

Detractors may say
>"but what if you get hurt and need to be carried"

>Wouldn't something furred be better for cold weather?

1:
>Skill issue
And 2:
>Heat dissipation is more important than insulation, since you will have access to fires, gas heaters, and clothing.
Any other combination besides the human pack mule and small scout lizard is objectively inferior.
